### 2. `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` Missing from `.env`
**File:** [.env](file:///c:/Users/DELL%20LATITUDE/Desktop/SecureGate/.env)

The primary `.env` file has **no `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` or `NEXTAUTH_URL`**. Only `.env.local` has them. In production (Vercel), environment variables come from the dashboard, not `.env.local`. If someone deploys using only `.env`, NextAuth will fail silently or use an insecure default.

**Fix:** Ensure `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` and `NEXTAUTH_URL` are set in the Vercel environment. Document this clearly.

