### 3. Weak Token Generation — `crypto.randomUUID()` Instead of `crypto.randomBytes()`
**File:** [token.ts](file:///c:/Users/DELL%20LATITUDE/Desktop/SecureGate/src/lib/token.ts)

```typescript
export function generateToken(): string {
  return crypto.randomUUID()  // ❌ Only 122 bits of entropy, predictable format
}
```

The AGENTS.md **explicitly requires** `crypto.randomBytes()` for verification and password reset tokens. `randomUUID()` produces a v4 UUID which, while random, has a predictable format (dashes, version nibble) and only 122 bits of randomness. The dev log also shows tokens that look like hex strings (64 chars), suggesting the code was previously using `randomBytes` but was changed.

**Fix:**
```typescript
import crypto from "crypto"
export function generateToken(): string {
  return crypto.randomBytes(32).toString("hex")
}
```

