### 5. Two Conflicting Database URLs
**Files:** [.env](file:///c:/Users/DELL%20LATITUDE/Desktop/SecureGate/.env) → Neon, [.env.local](file:///c:/Users/DELL%20LATITUDE/Desktop/SecureGate/.env.local) → Supabase

`.env` points to a **Neon** database, `.env.local` points to a **Supabase** database. Next.js loads `.env.local` with higher priority, so locally Supabase is used. But this creates confusion — which database has the actual schema/data? If the Prisma migrations were run against one but the app connects to the other, you'll get runtime errors.

**Fix:** Pick one database. Remove the other `DATABASE_URL`. Ensure migrations are run against the active database.

