## 🟠 High Issues

### 6. In-Memory Rate Limiter — Useless in Production (Serverless)
**File:** [rate-limit.ts](file:///c:/Users/DELL%20LATITUDE/Desktop/SecureGate/src/lib/rate-limit.ts)

```typescript
const store = new Map<string, { count: number; resetAt: number }>()
```

The rate limiter uses an **in-memory `Map`**. On Vercel (serverless), each function invocation gets a fresh memory space. The rate limit counter resets on every cold start, making it **completely ineffective** against brute-force attacks.

Additionally, the `setInterval` cleanup at line 28 will **leak in serverless** — it keeps the function alive and can cause unexpected behavior.

The `.env` files have **empty** `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL` and `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN`, suggesting the intent was to use Upstash Redis but it was never configured.

**Fix:** Implement rate limiting with Upstash Redis using `@upstash/ratelimit`, or at minimum document that the in-memory approach is dev-only.

