### 8. Signup Silently Succeeds for Existing Users — No Verification Email Resent
**File:** [signup/route.ts](file:///c:/Users/DELL%20LATITUDE/Desktop/SecureGate/src/app/api/auth/signup/route.ts#L27-L29)

```typescript
if (existingUser) {
  return NextResponse.json({ success: true })  // Silent success, no email sent
}
```

This correctly avoids leaking whether an email exists (good security), but creates a **UX dead end**: if a user tries to re-register with an unverified email, they get `{ success: true }` and are told to check their email — but **no verification email is actually sent**. They're stuck.

**Fix:** If `existingUser` exists and `!existingUser.emailVerified`, generate a new token and resend the verification email before returning success.

