### 9. `react-jsx` in tsconfig.json — Potential Conflict with Next.js
**File:** [tsconfig.json](file:///c:/Users/DELL%20LATITUDE/Desktop/SecureGate/tsconfig.json#L17)

```json
"jsx": "react-jsx"
```

Next.js normally uses `"jsx": "preserve"` so that SWC/Babel handles JSX transformation. Setting `"react-jsx"` can cause compilation issues, especially with React Server Components. This may be contributing to the build/caching errors seen in the dev log.

**Fix:** Change to `"jsx": "preserve"`.

