## 🟡 Medium Issues

### 11. API Routes Under `/api/auth/` Conflict with NextAuth
**Files:** All API routes under `src/app/api/auth/`

NextAuth uses the `/api/auth/*` namespace for its own routes (`/api/auth/signin`, `/api/auth/callback`, etc.). Placing custom routes like `/api/auth/signup`, `/api/auth/forgot-password` in the same namespace works but creates a **collision risk**. If NextAuth adds a route matching one of your custom names in a future version, it will silently break.

**Fix:** Consider moving custom auth routes to `/api/signup`, `/api/forgot-password`, etc. (outside the NextAuth namespace). Low risk currently, but worth noting.

