### 12. Password Strength Indicator Has a Logic Gap
**File:** [PasswordStrengthIndicator.tsx](file:///c:/Users/DELL%20LATITUDE/Desktop/SecureGate/src/components/auth/PasswordStrengthIndicator.tsx#L12-L21)

```typescript
if (password.length < 8 || typeCount <= 1) return { level: "weak" }
if (password.length >= 8 && typeCount >= 2 && password.length < 12) return { level: "fair" }
if (password.length >= 12 && typeCount >= 3) return { level: "strong" }
return { level: "weak" }  // Catches: length >= 12 with typeCount === 2
```

A password like `"AbcdefghijklABCD"` (16 chars, 2 types: upper + lower) falls through all conditions and returns "weak" — but it arguably meets "fair" criteria. The logic has gaps.

**Fix:** Make the conditions exhaustive or use a scoring system.

