### 15. Reset Password API Returns Inconsistent Error Shape
**File:** [reset-password/route.ts](file:///c:/Users/DELL%20LATITUDE/Desktop/SecureGate/src/app/api/auth/reset-password/route.ts)

- On invalid/expired token: returns `{ status: "INVALID_TOKEN" }` (no `error` field)
- On server error: returns `{ error: "Something went wrong..." }`

The client-side code in [reset-password/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/DELL%20LATITUDE/Desktop/SecureGate/src/app/reset-password/page.tsx#L53) checks `result.error`, so when the API returns `{ status: "INVALID_TOKEN" }`, the client **doesn't show any error toast** — it silently does nothing.

**Fix:** Standardize the API response shape. Always include an `error` field for error cases.

