### 16. Forgot Password Swallows Server Errors
**File:** [forgot-password/route.ts](file:///c:/Users/DELL%20LATITUDE/Desktop/SecureGate/src/app/api/auth/forgot-password/route.ts#L69-L72)

```typescript
} catch (error) {
  console.error("Forgot password error:", error)
  return NextResponse.json({ success: true })  // ← Swallows the error
}
```

On a server error (e.g., database down), the API returns `{ success: true }`, making debugging impossible from the client side. While this avoids leaking info, a generic error response with a 500 status would be more appropriate.

